    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-12-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <head>108. Memorandum From Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_BH_1"
                        >Brown</persName> to the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d108fn1">Source: Carter Library, National Security Affairs,
                            <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName> Material, Country
                        File, Box 30, Iran 12/10/79–12/31/79. Top Secret. A stamped notation at the
                        top of the memorandum reads: “<gloss target="#t_ZB_1">ZB</gloss> has
                        seen.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-12-19">December 19, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Force Posture During the Holiday Season (U)</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. (U) The purpose of this memorandum is to confirm our discussions of 19
                    December 1979 regarding force posture and response times during the holiday
                    season.</p>
                <p>2. (<gloss target="#t_TS_1">TS</gloss>) Training for the rescue option is
                    scheduled to be completed with a full-scale rehearsal on 21 December 1979.
                    Following successful completion of this rehearsal, combined training would be
                    suspended until about 7 January 1980 to provide the <gloss target="#t_Delta_1"
                        >Delta</gloss> team, Ranger and helicopter personnel with an opportunity to
                    return to their home bases <pb facs="0339" n="290" xml:id="pg_290"/> for the
                    holidays. Each of these groups will have a reassembly plan which will provide us
                    with the capability to reconstitute the rescue force within 24 hours. As a
                    result, our reaction time for the rescue option would be extended by a like
                    amount of time.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to the hostage crisis.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Harold Brown</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
